div class=3D"cell"><h2>Instructions</h2></div><div class=3D"cell"><h3>To ca=
lculate the number of days between any two dates (ie. the left hand form ab=
ove):</h3>
<p>Step 1 =E2=80=93 Choose your starting date<br>
Select the starting date of your choice using the drop-down arrows next to =
each selection box. When you open the Day Calculator, the date is automatic=
ally set to today=E2=80=99s date. As the calculator takes today=E2=80=99s d=
ate from your system clock, it is important to make sure that your system d=
ate is correctly set for this function to work properly.</p>
<p>Step 2 =E2=80=93 Choose your ending date<br>
Select the ending date of your choice using the drop-down arrows next to ea=
ch selection box. When you open the Day Calculator, the date is automatical=
ly set to today=E2=80=99s date. As the calculator takes today=E2=80=99s dat=
e from your system clock, it is important to make sure that your system dat=
