<p>Step 1 =E2=80=93 Choose your starting date<br>
Select the starting date of your choice using the drop-down arrows next to =
each selection box. When you open the Day Calculator, the date is automatic=
ally set to today=E2=80=99s date. As the calculator takes today=E2=80=99s d=
ate from your system clock, it is important to make sure that your system d=
ate is correctly set for this function to work properly.</p>
<p>Step 2 =E2=80=93 Choose whether to add or subtract<br>
Either select the radio button marked =E2=80=9CAdd=E2=80=9D or the radio bu=
tton marked =E2=80=9CSubtract=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p>Step 3 =E2=80=93 Type in the number of days to add or subtract<br>
This must be a whole number.</p>
<p>Step 4 =E2=80=93 Calculate<br>
Press the button marked =E2=80=9CCalculate=E2=80=9D to carry out the calcul=
ation. The new ending date will be displayed at the bottom of the form, inc=
luding the day of the week. Note that the calculation excludes the starting=
 date itself (ie. day number 1 is the day after your starting date) but inc=
ludes the ending date.</p>
